John L. Plueger  CEO, President & Director, Air Lease CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships63$7,785,065As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. John L. Plueger has been the President of Air Lease Corporation since March 2010 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since July 01, 2016. Mr. Plueger served as Chief Operating Officer of Air Lease Corporation since March 2010 until June 2016. He served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of International Lease Finance Corp. from 2002 to March 26, 2010 and served as its Acting Chief Executive Officer from February 3, 2010 to March 26, 2010. Mr. Plueger ... served as an Executive Vice President and Co-Chief Operating Officer of ILFC from 1995 to 2001. He served as Acting Head of aircraft-leasing unit of American International Group, Inc. until April 2010. He held other positions at ILFC since 1986. He has been a Director at Air Lease Corporation since March 2010 and Independent Director of Spirit AeroSystems Holdings, Inc. since July 29, 2014. He served as a Director of International Lease Finance Corporation since 2002 until March 26, 2010. He is a certified FAA Airline Transport pilot and instructor. Mr. Plueger received his Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of California, Los Angeles and is a Certified Director from the UCLA Anderson Graduate School of Management's Corporate Director Certification Program.Read Full Background




